WEBVTT

00:01:59.219 --> 00:02:01.521
Really, this just doesn't suit my style...

00:02:02.222 --> 00:02:04.290
to just sit and wait like this.

00:02:04.824 --> 00:02:07.494
We pick our spot, then wait patiently.

00:02:07.560 --> 00:02:09.662
That is the secret behind fishing.

00:02:10.330 --> 00:02:12.832
<i>Did you ever consider</i>
<i>that maybe this was the wrong spot?</i>

00:02:13.500 --> 00:02:17.570
-The bait has no right to complain.
-What are you fishing for?

00:02:18.238 --> 00:02:21.875
Starship Pirates.
A group that calls themselves pirates.

00:02:22.142 --> 00:02:23.443
Pirates?

00:02:23.510 --> 00:02:27.347
{\an8}People who like to attack a ship
and rob anything and everything from them.

00:02:27.881 --> 00:02:30.316
Like to rob, rob, drunken slob.

00:02:33.620 --> 00:02:36.456
<i>Besides, where the hell did Spike go?</i>

00:02:36.523 --> 00:02:38.825
<i>He left to overhaul his ship</i>
<i>and still hasn't--</i>

00:02:42.328 --> 00:02:43.463
Thanks.

00:02:44.531 --> 00:02:46.366
But, Spike, man...

00:02:47.534 --> 00:02:49.936
What's he doing now,
without giving us a heads-up?

00:03:09.689 --> 00:03:11.324
You're late, Doohan.

00:03:11.391 --> 00:03:14.260
Yeah! Go, go, go!

00:03:15.395 --> 00:03:16.262
Hey.

00:03:17.564 --> 00:03:18.698
Hey!

00:03:19.566 --> 00:03:21.334
<i>Strike three! Batter out!</i>

00:03:21.401 --> 00:03:24.370
<i>He just let that one slide by.</i>
<i>And that's the game.</i>

00:03:25.805 --> 00:03:29.208
Man, why didn't they just send in
a pinch hitter?

00:03:29.275 --> 00:03:31.811
Come on, Eightwood is getting old.

00:03:32.545 --> 00:03:33.413
Don't you think?

00:03:36.416 --> 00:03:37.350
Where's Doohan?

00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:41.788
The old man's kind of busy. I'm Miles,
his assistant. Nice to meet you.

00:03:50.763 --> 00:03:54.267
Man, they were really great
when they won the pennant 14 years ago.

00:03:54.334 --> 00:03:57.537
They just kept hitting the ball
and turned losing games around.

00:03:57.604 --> 00:04:02.308
Especially when Randy,
Blanket and Hills hit consecutive homers.

00:04:02.709 --> 00:04:04.477
I really wish you could've seen it.

00:04:05.011 --> 00:04:06.012
And you know...

00:04:08.314 --> 00:04:11.618
Hey, do people often say
you're the silent type?

00:04:12.652 --> 00:04:15.688
And people often say
you talk too much, right?

00:04:16.522 --> 00:04:17.390
Kind of.

00:04:18.258 --> 00:04:19.559
The... Swordfish, right?

00:04:20.326 --> 00:04:21.394
The machine back there.

00:04:22.028 --> 00:04:23.029
Yeah.

00:04:23.296 --> 00:04:26.366
That's the amazing MONO racer
that the old man built, right?

00:04:26.799 --> 00:04:29.969
It's just an old machine.
I don't want it, but it's a part of me.

00:04:30.036 --> 00:04:31.571
I hear you.

00:04:31.638 --> 00:04:34.874
Us Blue Sox fans feel
like we fell for some wicked broad.

00:04:34.941 --> 00:04:38.278
I can't remember how many times
I've thought about giving up on them.

00:04:57.730 --> 00:04:58.931
Jesus, not again.

00:05:00.800 --> 00:05:02.368
Yo, old man!

00:05:10.576 --> 00:05:12.779
-Yo. Long time no see.
-Yeah.

00:05:13.446 --> 00:05:15.048
Miles, where's the checklist?

00:05:15.315 --> 00:05:16.316
It's out there.

00:05:16.382 --> 00:05:17.650
I put it on the ship's body.

00:05:19.652 --> 00:05:22.789
He's been fixing that ancient thing?

00:05:22.855 --> 00:05:24.424
I think it's useless.

00:05:25.358 --> 00:05:27.927
The computer isn't compatible
with the MONO system.

00:05:27.994 --> 00:05:32.098
Miles! Give me the EV transmitter,
the absorber for the main gear

00:05:32.365 --> 00:05:35.368
and the 3-8 pneumatic tube.

00:05:35.435 --> 00:05:38.037
A 3-8?
I don't have something that special.

00:05:38.104 --> 00:05:41.607
Order one from Reggie. His place has them.

00:05:41.674 --> 00:05:45.645
Yeah, yeah.
You really are some slave driver.

00:05:49.015 --> 00:05:50.349
Some hobby.

00:05:57.790 --> 00:06:00.693
-Did we catch it?
-It wasn't me. Where is it?

00:06:00.760 --> 00:06:04.030
-It's close. Shit, I used bad bait.
-Hey!

00:06:09.602 --> 00:06:11.804
This is a good machine.

00:06:11.871 --> 00:06:15.675
Attacking blessed people like them
and giving to the poor

00:06:15.742 --> 00:06:19.445
<i>is human equality, don't you think so?</i>

00:06:20.680 --> 00:06:23.049
I get it.
This is what you call social reform.

00:06:23.116 --> 00:06:27.487
<i>Yeah. It's only right for us,</i>
<i>the poor, to take from them.</i>

00:06:29.756 --> 00:06:31.390
-Something's coming.
-Cops?

00:06:33.126 --> 00:06:35.528
Hi. That's enough.

00:06:35.595 --> 00:06:37.864
Bounty hunter?

00:06:37.930 --> 00:06:41.033
-Harman.
-Be a good girl and come here.

00:06:44.137 --> 00:06:45.671
Faye, above you!

00:06:51.410 --> 00:06:52.945
What the...? Is this a joke?

00:06:57.617 --> 00:06:58.651
It's not me!

00:06:59.986 --> 00:07:01.821
Ruth! One more behind us.

00:07:02.488 --> 00:07:04.190
<i>-And it's huge.</i>
-I know.

00:07:04.991 --> 00:07:06.959
What a tattered old ship.

00:07:07.026 --> 00:07:08.161
Leave me alone.

00:07:28.080 --> 00:07:31.751
<i>Abnormality found in the MONO system.</i>
<i>Booting the emergency pilot program.</i>

00:07:35.888 --> 00:07:38.124
Hey, stop this thing!

00:07:39.125 --> 00:07:40.193
Like I know how.

00:08:26.506 --> 00:08:28.674
Looks like he's taken you
on quite a few spins.

00:08:29.642 --> 00:08:30.510
Cut it.

00:08:36.148 --> 00:08:38.618
The accelerator pump is all worn down.

00:08:38.684 --> 00:08:39.752
I know.

00:08:39.819 --> 00:08:43.055
And the fuel injector
doesn't have a silencer on it.

00:08:43.789 --> 00:08:44.690
Don't need one.

00:08:45.291 --> 00:08:46.926
But it's noisy and it trembles...

00:08:46.993 --> 00:08:49.629
If you put one in,
I can't hear what it's telling me.

00:08:51.297 --> 00:08:53.199
Just hurry up and connect the injector.

00:08:54.534 --> 00:08:57.570
First of all, a 3-8 isn't popular anymore.

00:08:58.037 --> 00:09:00.940
Why don't you switch to the new 5-0?

00:09:01.007 --> 00:09:01.941
Miles.

00:09:02.008 --> 00:09:05.711
If you change the navigation to auto,
you glide along without manual steering.

00:09:08.180 --> 00:09:11.784
Do you want to use a machine,
or do you want the machine to use you?

00:09:11.851 --> 00:09:12.718
Which is it?

00:09:14.220 --> 00:09:15.688
-I wasn't exactly--
-Just go.

00:09:21.260 --> 00:09:22.628
You haven't changed a bit.

00:09:23.162 --> 00:09:26.065
At this rate,
another assistant is gonna leave you.

00:09:28.935 --> 00:09:33.039
And you.
The Swordfish wants to run away from you.

00:09:34.106 --> 00:09:35.207
I haven't heard that before.

00:09:35.274 --> 00:09:39.745
If you keep being reckless with her,
she'll really throw you off someday.

00:09:40.346 --> 00:09:43.616
Unfortunately,
I'm not one for delicate controls.

00:09:49.822 --> 00:09:51.090
Sorry to keep you waiting.

00:09:51.157 --> 00:09:54.594
I got something you don't see often...
A 3-8 pneumatic tube.

00:10:00.633 --> 00:10:02.335
Yes, hello?

00:10:03.035 --> 00:10:05.972
Oh, it's you, Missing Man.
Where are you right now?

00:10:06.639 --> 00:10:08.941
I'm still with Doohan. How's Jet?

00:10:09.008 --> 00:10:10.776
<i>He seems rather busy right now.</i>

00:10:11.377 --> 00:10:15.181
-Saying something about some bacteria.
-Bacteria?

00:10:15.881 --> 00:10:18.384
A virus. We got a computer virus.

00:10:19.251 --> 00:10:20.653
Same difference.

00:10:22.021 --> 00:10:25.057
Starting with the MONO system,
orbit calculator,

00:10:25.124 --> 00:10:28.728
flight-path selector, engine regulator,
communications circuit...

00:10:29.261 --> 00:10:30.329
<i>they're all shot.</i>

00:10:30.930 --> 00:10:33.232
I don't get it.
Give me a simple explanation.

00:10:33.933 --> 00:10:37.803
The computer broke,
and we're just drifting along.

00:10:39.338 --> 00:10:40.840
Well, I understood that.

00:10:40.906 --> 00:10:42.775
How about it? It's the newest one.

00:10:42.842 --> 00:10:44.810
You haven't seen one anywhere else, right?

00:10:44.877 --> 00:10:46.812
A MONO computer?

00:10:46.879 --> 00:10:49.915
How about it? 150K... No, 100K.

00:10:51.017 --> 00:10:52.284
A bargain, huh?

00:10:52.351 --> 00:10:54.887
When it's that cheap,
you lose money even on salvage.

00:10:54.954 --> 00:10:55.955
So, who did it?

00:10:56.422 --> 00:10:57.757
Where did you get this?

00:10:57.823 --> 00:10:59.859
A truck? Any features?

00:10:59.925 --> 00:11:01.260
-A penguin...
-...logo on...

00:11:01.327 --> 00:11:02.662
...the delivery truck?

00:11:15.841 --> 00:11:17.309
Are you sure about the info?

00:11:17.376 --> 00:11:20.379
Yeah. They apparently were dealing
at the Orbit Drive-in.

00:11:20.446 --> 00:11:25.217
I see. Nobody would be suspicious
of a delivery truck wandering about.

00:11:27.286 --> 00:11:29.221
And how are we going
to counter the hacks?

00:11:29.922 --> 00:11:31.223
Don't get harpooned.

00:11:36.228 --> 00:11:37.830
-And?
-That's it?

00:11:38.864 --> 00:11:41.167
They laughed this ship off as "tattered."

00:11:41.967 --> 00:11:44.370
And they made that mess
out of my Hammer Head.

00:11:45.204 --> 00:11:48.240
Unlike someone I know,
I always pay back what I owe.

00:11:49.008 --> 00:11:51.110
What a wonderful principle.

00:11:51.977 --> 00:11:53.479
I'm really not up for this.

00:11:54.780 --> 00:11:57.716
I have an invoice from Doohan here.

00:12:04.156 --> 00:12:07.293
Because they're physically
sending the virus,

00:12:07.359 --> 00:12:09.462
they haven't developed a vaccine for it.

00:12:09.728 --> 00:12:13.132
That is where this secret weapon
of ours comes in.

00:12:14.166 --> 00:12:16.836
What? That's just our normal communicator.

00:12:17.303 --> 00:12:20.906
If you get infected by the virus,
cut off the entire MONO system.

00:12:21.307 --> 00:12:23.476
All navigation
and communication will go down.

00:12:23.742 --> 00:12:26.912
As I said, I will navigate you with this.

00:12:27.313 --> 00:12:30.850
Because this is set to the frequency
for an old communications satellite,

00:12:30.916 --> 00:12:32.985
it has nothing to do
with the MONO system.

00:12:36.288 --> 00:12:40.292
<i>Oh, another run scored</i>
<i>against the Blue Sox.</i>

00:12:40.993 --> 00:12:42.995
That's some secret weapon.

00:13:12.491 --> 00:13:14.493
It was a penguin, right?

00:13:14.560 --> 00:13:17.263
Yeah. A purple penguin.

00:13:24.303 --> 00:13:25.538
There are two of them?

00:13:26.172 --> 00:13:29.074
Wait a minute.
It might be a real courier service.

00:13:29.141 --> 00:13:31.443
It's a matter of how to figure out
if they're legit.

00:13:32.111 --> 00:13:33.245
That's easy.

00:13:33.312 --> 00:13:35.848
We fire a shot.
The one that runs is the one we want.

00:13:36.315 --> 00:13:38.250
This is the first time I agree with you.

00:13:39.218 --> 00:13:40.452
You guys.

00:13:43.989 --> 00:13:46.825
What are you gonna do
if they're both real?

00:13:52.097 --> 00:13:53.399
<i>They both ran?</i>

00:13:53.999 --> 00:13:56.101
<i>We didn't consider that option.</i>

00:13:58.437 --> 00:14:02.074
-I'm trusting you with that one.
-I have to pay them back for yesterday.

00:14:20.626 --> 00:14:21.560
Forgive us.

00:14:22.294 --> 00:14:24.463
We'll pay the parking fee.

00:14:29.335 --> 00:14:30.202
This way?

00:14:31.003 --> 00:14:33.072
<i>Spike. Draw them out.</i>

00:14:33.639 --> 00:14:36.075
<i>It'll be a mess</i>
<i>if they let the virus go in there.</i>

00:14:36.141 --> 00:14:37.009
<i>I know.</i>

00:14:43.115 --> 00:14:44.416
So, let's see what you got.

00:14:48.454 --> 00:14:49.321
He's here.

00:14:49.922 --> 00:14:50.589
Waste of time.

00:15:02.268 --> 00:15:03.502
He's after the arm.

00:15:03.569 --> 00:15:05.504
He's not taking us seriously. Ruth.

00:15:06.171 --> 00:15:07.106
Ready to go anytime.

00:15:08.574 --> 00:15:10.209
Take that!

00:15:12.311 --> 00:15:13.445
Welcome.

00:15:16.916 --> 00:15:18.050
Excellent.

00:15:21.654 --> 00:15:22.688
Bingo!

00:15:25.524 --> 00:15:27.059
He's holding up pretty well.

00:15:35.501 --> 00:15:37.603
-Cut off the MONO system!
-I'm doing it!

00:15:42.541 --> 00:15:45.978
That idiot cut off his MONO system.

00:15:46.045 --> 00:15:47.179
Hey, George.

00:15:47.246 --> 00:15:49.481
And he's in Earth's gravitational field.

00:15:56.188 --> 00:15:58.023
Old man! Here, here!

00:15:58.090 --> 00:16:00.960
-This is pretty bad!
<i>-Align the D7. You did it before, right?</i>

00:16:01.026 --> 00:16:02.194
<i>Like I remember.</i>

00:16:02.661 --> 00:16:04.363
No good. There's nothing we can do.

00:16:08.000 --> 00:16:10.502
You idiot.
Hurry up and do something about this.

00:16:10.569 --> 00:16:13.305
Damn it. Move! Move!

00:16:14.106 --> 00:16:15.641
Falling! We're falling!

00:16:19.745 --> 00:16:21.213
Spike, I'll be right there.

00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:23.716
<i>I'm calculating an interception course.</i>

00:16:23.983 --> 00:16:26.418
<i>Until then, somehow keep control manually.</i>

00:16:27.219 --> 00:16:30.222
<i>Even if everything was normal,</i>
<i>it'd be tough to get out of here.</i>

00:16:31.523 --> 00:16:33.158
I can see that.

00:16:37.229 --> 00:16:39.999
And I just had it overhauled.

00:16:44.236 --> 00:16:46.305
Oh, well. Whatever happens happens.

00:16:56.448 --> 00:16:57.383
<i>Spike, above you.</i>

00:16:59.385 --> 00:17:01.320
Your tattered ship looks like a goddess.

00:17:14.633 --> 00:17:16.101
Shit, the virus.

00:17:19.738 --> 00:17:21.240
-Spike!
<i>-I'm still alive.</i>

00:17:21.707 --> 00:17:23.042
<i>We have to start over.</i>

00:17:30.449 --> 00:17:32.551
No way. Old man, you gotta be kidding.

00:17:32.618 --> 00:17:35.421
Are you really gonna move
this ancient piece of...?

00:17:35.487 --> 00:17:37.589
Do you think I'd do this as a joke?

00:17:42.694 --> 00:17:46.065
Don't just stand there.
Hurry up and get me some fuel.

00:17:46.465 --> 00:17:47.332
All right.

00:17:48.434 --> 00:17:51.270
Spike, can you hear me?
I got a calculation.

00:17:51.770 --> 00:17:54.339
It'll take another seven hours
for us to rendezvous.

00:17:55.107 --> 00:17:56.708
Come on, you're joking, right?

00:17:57.342 --> 00:18:00.846
<i>We're too close to Earth.</i>
<i>The orbital paths I can take are limited.</i>

00:18:01.113 --> 00:18:03.182
Isn't there a way for you
to just swing on by?

00:18:03.248 --> 00:18:05.084
<i>If I plunge in at this angle,</i>

00:18:05.150 --> 00:18:07.653
<i>both The Bebop and the Swordfish</i>
<i>will burn to nothing.</i>

00:18:24.803 --> 00:18:25.737
Jet.

00:18:27.739 --> 00:18:29.775
<i>I have some booze hidden</i>
<i>behind the fridge.</i>

00:18:30.542 --> 00:18:31.643
<i>Feel free to drink some.</i>

00:18:32.678 --> 00:18:33.545
Something wrong?

00:18:34.780 --> 00:18:37.549
I'm out of gas. Nothing I can do now.

00:18:38.717 --> 00:18:42.321
<i>How about I go there and tow you back,</i>
<i>in exchange for that booze?</i>

00:18:42.888 --> 00:18:47.226
I heard the conversation.
Give me the Swordfish's<i> </i>coordinates.

00:18:47.693 --> 00:18:50.395
Doohan? How the hell do you...?

00:19:12.885 --> 00:19:16.522
<i>Spike, I don't care how you do it,</i>
<i>but slow down using an air brake.</i>

00:19:16.588 --> 00:19:17.456
Slow down?

00:19:17.523 --> 00:19:20.259
If you slow down
within Earth's atmosphere,

00:19:20.325 --> 00:19:22.794
the gravitational pull
will accelerate you instead,

00:19:23.629 --> 00:19:25.597
<i>which will give you enough speed</i>
<i>to escape.</i>

00:19:25.664 --> 00:19:28.400
<i>However, you have to maintain the ship</i>
<i>at a certain angle.</i>

00:19:28.467 --> 00:19:31.870
<i>Too far either way, and you'll be thrown</i>
<i>to the other end of the universe.</i>

00:19:31.937 --> 00:19:34.406
Unfortunately,
I'm not one for delicate controls.

00:19:35.507 --> 00:19:36.441
<i>Spike...</i>

00:19:37.743 --> 00:19:39.244
I know you can do it.

00:19:39.745 --> 00:19:42.381
I didn't give you the Swordfish
for nothing.

00:19:45.417 --> 00:19:47.753
Don't you start crashing, either.

00:20:03.936 --> 00:20:05.404
Maximum propulsion.

00:20:06.738 --> 00:20:08.974
You didn't have to force yourself
to come with me.

00:20:09.908 --> 00:20:12.544
You know how Blue Sox fans
love to party.

00:20:15.480 --> 00:20:17.382
-Let's go.
-All right.

00:20:40.639 --> 00:20:41.673
We're flying.

00:20:43.408 --> 00:20:45.244
We're really flying.

00:20:55.754 --> 00:20:57.389
<i>Lower the nose by 0.6 degrees.</i>

00:21:05.797 --> 00:21:06.965
<i>You're in too deep.</i>

00:21:07.032 --> 00:21:08.567
<i>Spike, you'll burn to a crisp.</i>

00:21:14.806 --> 00:21:15.941
<i>This is the last chance.</i>

00:21:35.661 --> 00:21:38.764
It went in. It went in! That was perfect!

00:21:40.932 --> 00:21:42.401
Doohan, you saved me.

00:21:42.467 --> 00:21:43.568
<i>Not quite.</i>

00:21:43.635 --> 00:21:46.004
Most of the heat-resistant tiles
have peeled off.

00:21:46.071 --> 00:21:47.539
The temperature is rising.

00:21:48.473 --> 00:21:49.975
<i>The landing gear isn't coming down.</i>

00:21:50.042 --> 00:21:51.877
<i>Oh yeah, and the 2 nozzle won't work.</i>

00:21:51.943 --> 00:21:54.913
<i>What?! Is that for real?!</i>
<i>What are we gonna do?!</i>

00:21:54.980 --> 00:21:59.084
<i>-We can't land without them!</i>
-Oh, well. Whatever happens happens.

00:21:59.351 --> 00:22:02.754
<i>I knew I shouldn't have come up here!</i>
<i>I'm still too young to die!</i>

00:22:34.019 --> 00:22:39.057
<i>Too much time has passed by</i>

00:22:39.591 --> 00:22:43.962
<i>To lament that we were deeply in love</i>

00:22:45.964 --> 00:22:51.002
<i>The wind keeps blowing, while my heart</i>

00:22:52.037 --> 00:22:56.608
<i>Cannot heal all the tears in it</i>

00:22:58.577 --> 00:23:05.584
<i>Someone cry for me with parched eyes.</i>

00:23:09.020 --> 00:23:12.124
<i>The real folk blues</i>

00:23:12.758 --> 00:23:15.861
<i>I only want to know</i>

00:23:16.762 --> 00:23:20.832
<i>What true sadness is</i>

00:23:20.899 --> 00:23:23.835
<i>Sitting in muddy water</i>

00:23:24.736 --> 00:23:27.072
<i>Isn't such a bad life</i>

00:23:28.540 --> 00:23:35.547
<i>If it ends</i>

00:23:38.183 --> 00:23:41.586
<i>After the first time</i>

00:24:22.127 --> 00:24:25.864
<i>Next episode: "Pierrot le Fou."</i>

